  "prompt": "How can your remove white underarm stains from shirts?",
  "response": "Removing white underarm stains from shirts can be achieved through several methods, using common household items. Here are some effective techniques:\n\n### 1. **Baking Soda Paste**\n- **Ingredients**: Baking soda, water\n- **Method**:\n  1. Mix 1/4 cup of baking soda with a few tablespoons of water to form a paste.\n  2. Apply the paste directly to the stained area.\n  3. Let it sit for 30 minutes to an hour.\n  4. Wash the shirt in the hottest water safe for the fabric.\n\n### 2. **White Vinegar**\n- **Ingredients**: White vinegar\n- **Method**:\n  1. Pour white vinegar directly onto the stain.\n  2. Let it sit for about 30 minutes.\n  3. Wash the shirt as usual.\n\n### 3. **Lemon Juice and Baking Soda**\n- **Ingredients**: Lemon juice, baking soda\n- **Method**:\n  1. Mix equal parts of lemon juice and baking soda to form a paste.\n  2. Apply to the stained area.\n  3. Allow it to sit for about 30 minutes.\n  4. Rinse with cold water and wash as usual.\n\n### 4. **Hydrogen Peroxide**\n- **Ingredients**: Hydrogen peroxide (3%)\n- **Method**:\n  1. Apply hydrogen peroxide directly to the stain.\n  2. Let it sit for about 30 minutes before rinsing.\n  3. Wash the shirt normally.\n\n### 5. **Dish Soap and Hydrogen Peroxide**\n- **Ingredients**: Dish soap, hydrogen peroxide\n- **Method**:\n  1. Mix 1 part dish soap, 2 parts hydrogen peroxide.\n  2. Apply the mixture to the stain.\n  3. Allow it to sit for about 30 minutes.\n  4. Rinse and wash as usual.\n\n### 6. **Commercial Stain Removers**\n- Use a commercial stain remover following the manufacturer's instructions. Apply it to the stained area, let it sit for the recommended amount of time, and wash.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Always test any cleaning solution on an inconspicuous area of the fabric first to avoid discoloration.\n- Avoid using hot water on stains before treating them, as it can set the stain. Use cold or warm water instead.\n- If the stain doesn't come out completely after the first attempt, you may need to repeat the process before drying the shirt, as heat can set the stain.\n\nFollowing these methods can help you effectively remove white underarm stains from your shirts!",
